13/05/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Speaking on Croatia's national broadcasting network on Friday (May 11th), US Undersecretary of State Nicholas Burns suggested that Croatia would be invited to join NATO next year, during the Alliance's summit in Bucharest.
Burns, who was in Zagreb for a regional co-operation forum, said he was expressing the position of US President George W. Bush and Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice.
(Vjesnik, Vecernji list - 12/05/07;
HRT, Reuters - 11/05/07)
